Bag module¶

class Bag.Bag(param: Optional[Any] = None)¶

Bases: object

Multiset Data Structure

Unordered collection of elements where repetitions are allowed.

Implemented as an Array List that gets expanded as needed
current_size¶

Stores how many elements are in the bag

Type

int

array_list¶

ArrayList Data Structure that contains the data from bag

Type

list

Merge bag and iterator

When this bag is added with an iterator, merge both into bag. Otherwise, simply add element to bag

Returns

Return type

Hint

__hash__() → int¶

Generate a hash of this Bag using FNV1A hash

Makes a copy of this Bag and uses FNV1A hash with a little tweak (I use modulo 1E19 just so numbers don’t get TOO big)

Returns

Return type

int

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)

__init__(param: Optional[Any] = None) → NoReturn¶

Bag constructor

Parameters

any – integer, Bag or iterator that is used to populate the bag’s array list

Raises

TypeError – Occurs when param is not an integer, iterator nor other Bag

Example

>>> bag1 = Bag()
>>> bag1
[]
>>> bag2 = Bag([1,2,3])
>>> bag2
[1,2,3]
>>> bag3 = Bag(bag2)
>>> bag3
[1,2,3]

add(element: Any) → NoReturn¶

Adds new element

Before adding element, expand array list if necessary

Parameters

any – The element to be added to Bag

Returns

True if operation was successful

Return type

bool

Example

>>> bag = Bag()
>>> bag
[]
>>> bag.add(0)
True
>>> bag
[0]
>>> bag.add(3)
True
>>> bag
[0, 3]
>>> bag.add(10)
True
>>> bag
[0, 3, 10]

Hint

Average Time complexity: O(1)
Worst-case Time complexity: O(n)

clear() → NoReturn¶

Clear bag

Simply delete the array_list followed by making a new array_list with the same capacity as before filled with “None”

Example

>>> bag = Bag([1,2,3,4,3])
>>> bag
[1, 2, 3, 4, 3]
>>> bag.clear()
True
>>> bag
[]

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)

contains(element: Any) → bool¶

Test for element membership

Checks if the passed element is inside this bag. Implemented with Linear Search

Parameters

any – Element that is looked for in bag

Returns

True if element is inside bag

Return type

bool

Example

>>> bag = Bag([1,2,3])
>>> bag.contains(2)
True
>>> bag.contains(100)
False

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)

contract() → NoReturn¶

Contract array list capacity with which the Bag is implemented

Halves the capacity of the array list by making a new Bag, adding all this bag’s elements to the new Bag and, copying the new bag’s array list to this one

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)

count(element: Any) → int¶

Count copies of element

Perform Linear Search and add to counter when element is found

Parameters

any – Value whose count will be found

Returns

Amount of times element was found

Return type

int

Example

>>> bag = Bag([1,2,3,2,2])
>>> bag.count(2)
3

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)

expand() → NoReturn¶

Expand array list capacity with which the Bag is implemented

Duplicates the capacity of the array list by making a new Bag, adding all this bag’s elements to the new Bag and, copying the new bag’s array list to this one

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)
